Taken from https://www.tutorialsteacher.com/javascript/script-tag

==> the javascript code should be written in the <script> tag in HTML.
==> there can be multiple scripts in the head and the body of HTML. 
==> a JS function is a block of code which is executed when called.
==> a function is placed in the head or function of the body and is executed 
    when a button is clicked.
==> scripts can also be placed as external files, with the .js extension.

#First Script

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>JavaScript by Ishita</h2>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "Hello! this is popup from JavaScript!";
</script>

</body>
</html> 

Output

JavaScript by Ishita
Hello! this is popup from JavaScript!
